**Overall Meaning:**

This verse describes the state of liberation achieved through steadfast meditation. It states that one who attains liberation while living (Jivanmukti) remains liberated even after death.  Through unwavering focus in meditation, the seeker transcends duality and experiences the true nature of the Self.

**Translation:**

**Whose liberation occurs while living, even after death, he is liberated.  Attaining steadfastness in meditation, you become without duality, O sinless one.** 
